Text:
@nignug
I own every HL game (HL1+expansions and Orange Box), so it wasnt a problem for me i was just pointing out the stuff to other people.

And YES! i was playing it now and its awesome - coming back to Black Mesa facility after so many years and seeing it in new graphics... DELIGHT! it has everything HL1 had - recognizable voices, comedy, clickable stuff... and most of all - it still has the most important thing - MOOD!!! it still above and all Half Life 1 game... when they will finish it - it playable only till Lambda Core level (guys are working hard to recreate Xen levels which is hard aparently), its around 8hrs gameplay, still longer than most shooters now - i'll replay it again and HL2+episodes after that to give me one cohesive cinematic experience... All in all you can clearly see the love the makers of this have for HL franchise... if you like HL games i highly recommend this
